                <h1>Discover the Groove: Exploring Funk Music</h1>
                <p>Funk is a vibrant genre of music blending jazz, soul, and R&B, known for its groovy bass lines and danceable rhythms. It emerged in the 1960s and has evolved, influencing various styles. Funk celebrates individuality and corporate expression through lively performances. Iconic artists include James Brown, George Clinton, and Prince.</p>
